# GNAR — sway config for the rack touch-panel kiosk.
#
# Replaces mango: sway exposes wl_touch, so foot turns a tap into a click and
# gnar-board's on-screen buttons + tap-to-fullscreen work; it also hides the
# cursor for touch. Launched by ~/.zprofile on tty1 when a display is
# attached. The six dashboard panels are tiled into a 3x2 grid by
# gnar-kiosk-tiles (sway has no auto-grid layout).

### appearance — Tokyo Night; a thin 2px border + gaps is the only chrome
### (gnar-board renders its panels borderless, edge-to-edge).
output * bg #000000 solid_color
default_orientation horizontal
default_border pixel 2
default_floating_border pixel 2
font pango:monospace 8
gaps inner 6
gaps outer 8
smart_gaps off
#                        border  bg      text    indicator child_border
client.focused          #7dcfff #000000 #c0caf5 #7dcfff #3b4261
client.focused_inactive #3b4261 #000000 #565f89 #3b4261 #3b4261
client.unfocused        #3b4261 #000000 #565f89 #3b4261 #3b4261

### input — hide the cursor shortly after it stops moving (touch panel).
seat * hide_cursor 1500

### dashboard tiles
for_window [app_id="gnar-.*"] border pixel 2
exec gnar-kiosk-tiles

### walk-up keybindings (only matter with a keyboard plugged in)
bindsym Mod4+f fullscreen toggle
bindsym Mod4+Shift+r reload
bindsym Mod4+Shift+q exit
